20
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:25,205
{\an8}As it was is now
and ever shall be.

21
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:26,253
{\an8}What are you
getting at?

22
00:01:26,336 --> 00:01:27,586
{\an8}Well, you're always
trying to teach me

23
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:30,220
{\an8}to be open-minded.
Try new things, live life to--

24
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:31,838
{\an8}What are you talking about?
Nobody's trying to teach you that.

25
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:34,505
{\an8}-(sputtering)
-Ha! Ha! Ha-ha-ha!

26
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:36,264
{\an8}-Shut up, boy.
-Well, maybe Lisa's right.

27
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,886
{\an8}Tomorrow night, it might be nice to
go out for dinner.

28
00:01:38,973 --> 00:01:41,733
Tomorrow night? Friday?
Pork chop night?

29
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,100
Marge, we haven't missed
pork chop night

30
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:46,017
