in '87.

31
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:47,896
(sighs)
Friday night, pork chops.

32
00:01:47,982 --> 00:01:50,072
From cradle to grave,
etched in stone

33
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:52,071
in God's library
somewhere up in heaven.

34
00:01:52,153 --> 00:01:54,033
Okay, okay, okay, okay.
Where do you want to go?

35
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:56,874
Anywhere but hamburgers,
pizza or fried chicken.

36
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,620
Fine. We'll go to Mars.

37
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:01,121
There's that new
sushi restaurant on Elm Street.

38
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:03,214
Sushi? Hey maybe this is
just one of those things

39
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:06,499
you hear on the playground,
but isn't that raw fish?

40
00:02:06,584 --> 00:02:08,504
As usual, the playground
has the facts right,

41
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:10,376
but missed the point entirely.

42
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:12,973
Sushi is considered
quite a delicacy.

43
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:14,929
-Please, Homer. Can't we try it?
-No!

44
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:17,349
Please Dad, this argument
humiliates us both.

45
00:02:17,428 --> 00:02:18,968
If I said no the first time,

46
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:21,595
what makes you think I'm gonna
say yes the second time?

47
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,733
Nothing, but you may say yes
the 99th time.

48
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:24,640
Oh? Try me.

49
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:25,897
-Please, Dad.
-No.

50
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,189
-Please, Dad? Please, Dad?
-No. No.

51
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:29,192
-Please, Dad? Please, Dad?
-No. No.

52
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,284
-Please, Dad.
-Oh, okay, okay.

53
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:36,816
