by a blind woodsman.

82
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:39,795
Hang your head in shame.

83
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:40,926
(sighs)

84
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:48,142
Good thing I'm open-minded.

85
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:52,612
Not bad.
Interesting.

86
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:55,900
Let's try
this little pink one here.

87
00:03:55,985 --> 00:03:58,145
Mmm, very good.
And another one.

88
00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:01,068
Oh, boy, this fish
is delish.

89
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:07,907
(nervously)
Hi, my name is Richie Sakai.

90
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,377
I'm an anesthesiologist,

91
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:13,748
and I'd like to dedicate
this next song

92
00:04:13,836 --> 00:04:15,296
to my wife, Patty.

93
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:20,393
<i>♪ I was born in the wagon</i>
<i>of a traveling show ♪</i>

94
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:22,888
<i>♪ Mama used to dance</i>
<i>for the money they'd throw ♪</i>

95
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:27,811
<i>♪ Papa would do</i>
<i>whatever he could ♪</i>

96
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:30,102
Oh, ooh! And two
of these things.

97
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:32,106
-Two uni?
-And, ooh, ooh,

98
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:34,568
I don't believe I've tried
the flying fish roll.

99
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,529
I recommend it with
a roe quail egg on top.

100
00:04:36,609 --> 00:04:37,989
You're the doctor.

101
00:04:38,069 --> 00:04:41,739
<i>♪♪ (Theme from "Shaft")</i>

102
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,573
<i>♪ Who's the black</i>
<i>private dick ♪</i>

103
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:46,288
<i>♪ That's the sex machine</i>
<i>to all the chicks? ♪</i>

104
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,449
<i>♪ Shaft ♪</i>

105
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,287
<i>♪ You're damn right ♪</i>

106
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:51,582
♪ <i>Who's the cat</i>
<i>that won't cop out ♪</i>

107
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:54,286
<i>♪ When there's danger</i>
<i>all about? ♪</i>

108
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:56,087
<i>♪ Shaft ♪</i>

109
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,880
<i>♪ Right on ♪</i>

110
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,514
There's got to be something
I haven't tried. Huh?

111
00:05:00,591 --> 00:05:02,721
Hey, what's this?
Fugu.

112
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,472
(gasps)
It is blowfish, sir,

113
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:07,135
but I should warn you
that one--

114
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:11,103
Come on, pal.
Fugu me!

115
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:13,805
<i>♪ They say this cat Shaft</i>
<i>is a bad mother-- ♪</i>

116
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:15,606
<i>♪ Shut your mouth ♪</i>

117
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:16,730
<i>♪ But I'm</i>
<i>talkin' about Shaft ♪</i>

118
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:19,146
<i>♪ Then I can dig it ♪</i>

119
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:21,105
<i>♪ He's a complicated man ♪</i>

120
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:24,565
<i>♪ But no one understands</i>
<i>him but his woman ♪</i>

121
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,197
<i>♪ John Shaft ♪</i>

122
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,874
-(horn honks)
-Oh, she's here.

123
00:05:28,953 --> 00:05:30,793
Cover for me.

124
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,252
-One fugu.
-(gasping)

125
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:35,082
Not fugu. If it is
cut improperly it's--

126
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:37,588
Yes, yes, it is poisonous,
potentially fatal,

127
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:41,340
but, if sliced properly,
it can be quite tasty.

128
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:43,094
I must get master.

129
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:47,599
Oh... oh... oh,
Miss Krabappel.

130
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:51,560
Oh, your hair smells so...
so clean.

131
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:54,402
Uh, master, you are needed
in the kitchen.

132
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,399
I said cover for me,
damn it!

133
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,981
But, master,
we need your skilled hands.

134
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,397
My skilled hands are busy.
You do it!

135
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:05,494
Hmm, hmm...

136
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:07,283
(sighs)

137
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,577
Poison, poison. Tasty fish.

138
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:17,131
Concentrate.
Concentrate.

139
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,750
HOMER:
I want fugu!

140
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:24,511
Mmm. Fan-fugu-tastic.

141
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:26,762
(whistling)

142
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:30,008
Oh, no!

143
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:34,016
(yelling in Japanese)

144
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,650
Beautiful language,
isn't it, Marge?

145
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,822
For God's sake,
don't eat another bite.

146
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,241
Oh, I couldn't possibly.

147
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:45,779
Mr. Simpsonsan,
I shall be blunt.

148
00:06:45,863 --> 00:06:48,203
We have reason to believe
you have eaten...

149
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:50,452
-poison.
-Poison! Wha!

150
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:52,575
What should I do? What should I do?
Tell me quick.

151
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:54,292
Oh, no need to panic.

152
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,832
There's a map to the hospital
on the back of the menu.

153
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,286
(siren wailing)

154
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,496
Try something new, Homer.

155
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:02,586
What will it hurt you, Homer?

156
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,882
I never heard of
a poison pork chop.

157
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:07,636
Um, your wife agreed that
I should break this to you.

158
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:08,848
No need, doc.

159
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,508
I can read Marge like a book.

160
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,886
(groans)

161
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:14,524
Whoo! It's good news,
isn't it?

162
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,140
-No, Mr. Simpson.
-Oh.

163
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:18,647
If in fact you've consumed
the venom of the blowfish--

164
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:21,649
and from what the chef has
told me, it's quite probable--

165
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:24,742
You have 24 hours to live.

166
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:27,489
-24 hours!
-Well, 22.

167
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:28,992
I'm sorry
I kept you waiting so long.

168
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,413
Oh, Marge

169
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,371
I'm gonna die.
I'm gonna die.

170
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,582
(sobbing)

171
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:35,541
Well, if there's
one consolation

172
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:38,121
it's that you'll feel
no pain at all

173
00:07:38,207 --> 00:07:39,417
until some time
tomorrow evening

174
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,250
when your heart
suddenly explodes.

175
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:43,745
Now a little death anxiety
is normal.

176
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,588
You can expect to go through
five stages.

177
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:46,973
The first is denial.

178
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:48,799
No way,
because I'm not dying.

179
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:50,385
-Second is anger.
-Why, you little--

180
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,140
(stammering)

181
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:53,391
Then after that
comes fear.

182
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,063
What's after fear?
What's after fear?

183
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,101
-Bargaining.
-Doc, you gotta get me out of this.

184
00:07:57,185 --> 00:07:58,305
I'll make it
worth your while.

185
00:07:58,394 --> 00:07:59,984
And finally, acceptance.

186
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:02,152
Well, we all got to go sometime.

187
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:04,151
Mr. Simpson, your progress
astounds me.

188
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,283
I should leave you two alone.

189
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,070
Perhaps this pamphlet
will be helpful.

190
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:12,065
(Homer reading)

191
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:20,461
(sobbing)

192
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:23,211
Hello, Marge, hello.

193
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,554
I'm the one who's
dying, not you.

194
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:28,720
(sniffles)
Oh, I'm sorry, Homer.

195
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:30,429
Have you thought
about what you want

196
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,590
to tell the kids?

197
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:33,757
Nothing.
It'll just upset them.

198
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,466
I want my last hours
of family life

199
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:37,136
to be happy ones.

200
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:40,975
Well, have you decided
what you want to do tomorrow?

201
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:41,982
Almost.

202
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:44,153
(Marge muttering)

203
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:46,692
Oh, good. Aw!

204
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:50,316
I'm not done yet, Marge.

205
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:53,664
What's that word you use
for when you and I--

206
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:56,291
-You know.
-When we're intimate?

207
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,449
Be intimate with Marge.

208
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:01,038
Aw... Can I just make
one suggestion?

209
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:03,793
Can we get up early and
watch the sunrise together?

210
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:07,206
Ah... watch the sunrise.

211
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:11,876
Till 6:00 a.m.,
my dearest darling,

212
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,258
and my last day
on Earth.

213
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:17,847
(alarm beeping)

214
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:20,562
(snoring)

215
00:09:25,314 --> 00:09:26,864
11:30!

216
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:28,531
Oh, that's just great.

217
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:30,859
Marge, why did you
let me sleep so late?

218
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:32,485
You looked so peaceful
lying there.

219
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,912
There'll be plenty
of time for that!

220
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:36,581
I got tons of important
stuff to do.

221
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,079
Bart. Bart!

222
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,290
"Have man-to-man with Bart."

223
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:43,665
Come here, boy.

224
00:09:43,749 --> 00:09:44,709
Oh, man.

225
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:47,455
No!

226
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:49,875
I just want to have
a heart-to-heart talk.

227
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:52,174
-Oh.
-You know, Bart,

228
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,258
after me, you're the man
around the house.

229
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:56,553
And that means you're
gonna have to help out--

230
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,217
Aw, come on, I do
plenty around here.

231
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,056
Lisa never lifts a finger
Why don't you go yell at her?

232
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:03,481
Shut up, Bart!
This is good stuff.

233
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:05,441
I want to share
something with you.

234
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:08,441
The three little sentences that
will get you through life.

235
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:10,994
Number one--
Cover for me.

236
00:10:11,068 --> 00:10:13,488
Number two--
Oh, good idea, boss.

237
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:14,991
Number three--

238
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:16,822
It was like that
when I got here.

239
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:18,987
-Hey, this is good stuff.
-Told 'ya. Now c'mon.

240
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:20,366
You're going to learn
how to shave.

241
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:25,923
And finally, the little spot
under your nose.

242
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,090
Next, we take
some toilet paper,

243
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:31,210
tear off some
teensy little squares

244
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:34,967
and stick one there...
and there...

245
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,681
and anyplace
you're bleeding.

246
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,261
There and there.
Don't worry.

247
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:40,176
The blood will hold it
right on your face.

248
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:43,394
And now... some aftershave.

249
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:45,596
Oooh! Ahh! Eee! Ahhh!

250
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:48,436
Hnnn!
Ooh, ahh!

251
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:50,192
Son of a-- oh!

252
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,984
-And that's how we shave.
-Ooh--

253
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,568
-(glass breaks)
-D'oh!

254
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:54,823
-Oh!
-Why, you little--

255
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:56,414
It was like that
when I got here.

256
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:59,739
Oh, that's my boy.

257
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:03,155
"Listen to Lisa play her sax."

258
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,865
<i>♪♪ (saxophone)</i>

259
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:06,115
Hi, Dad.

260
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:08,127
Want me to cut out
this infernal racket?

261
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,999
Oh, let me hear you play.

262
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,296
-Why?
-Does a father have to explain?

263
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,920
Let's just share your gift.
Okay?

264
00:11:15,007 --> 00:11:17,127
<i>♪♪ (somber blues)</i>

265
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:18,468
Oh!

266
00:11:20,554 --> 00:11:22,184
(sobs)

267
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:27,515
<i>-♪♪ ("When the Saints Go Marchin' In")</i>
-Huh?

268
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,443
Yeah, that's
more like it.

269
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:33,533
Ho-ho! Whoo!

270
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:38,069
<i>♪ Oh, I want to be</i>
<i>in that number ♪</i>

271
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:41,945
<i>♪ When the saints</i>
<i>go over there ♪</i>

272
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,994
<i>♪ Oh, over there! ♪</i>

273
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:47,078
<i>♪ Oh,</i>
<i>over there! ♪</i>

274
00:11:47,164 --> 00:11:50,794
(Homer humming)

275
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:53,126
"Make videotape for Maggie."

276
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,882
(doorbell rings)

277
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,724
Simpson, what
a pleasant surprise.

278
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,219
We were just
pulling taffy.

279
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,220
Gee, the fun never stops
at the Flanders house,

280
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:02,392
-does it?
-No siree, Bob.

281
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:04,681
Hey, Flanders, could I
borrow your camcorder?

282
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:05,725
Okie-dokle.

283
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:09,899
Hey, why don't you
your family

284
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,479
come over for a
barbecue tomorrow?

285
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,404
-No, thanks.
-Oh, are you sure?

286
00:12:13,482 --> 00:12:15,782
We got that new propane beauty
just sittin' in the back yard.

287
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,650
-No, I don't--
-It's crying out

288
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:18,737
to cook up
some good eatin'.

289
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,871
Flanders!
I said I didn't--

290
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:22,198
Tomorrow?

291
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,453
Sure, what the hey.

292
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:26,945
I'd love to come
to your barbecue.

293
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:28,497
Heh-heh-heh.

294
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:32,501
I'll even bring the thickest,
juiciest T-bones

295
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:33,535
you've ever seen.

296
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:35,667
Mm-mm,
sounds terrif.

297
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,715
(chuckling)
The joke's on him.

298
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,048
I'll be dead by then.

299
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,683
(Homer muttering)

300
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,140
Is that it?

301
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:43,469
(clears throat)

302
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:46,684
This is a videotape
for my daughter, Maggie.

303
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:48,636
Hi, Maggie.

304
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:51,186
I'm speaking to you
from beyond the grave.

305
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,940
Whoo-hoo!

306
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,113
(laughs)

307
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:56,571
Hope that didn't scare you.

308
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,610
Well, Maggie,
you're grown up now,

309
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:01,284
and unless you taped over this,
you're probably wondering

310
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:03,533
what kind of man
your father was.

311
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,616
He was a simple man.
A kind man.

312
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:08,331
A gentle man who loved
his children and--

313
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:09,542
-(phone rings)
-D'oh!

314
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:10,662
(angrily)
Hello!

315
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:12,708
Yeah, he's here.
Who is this?

316
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,252
Bart's friend, Milhouse?

317
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:16,205
Bart, get your
butt down here!

318
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:17,295
(tires screech)

319
00:13:22,259 --> 00:13:23,969
-Dad?
-Huh?

320
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,473
Oh, it's you.
What do you want?

321
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:27,934
Dad, we've never been
too close, have we?

322
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:29,225
Not to my knowledge.

323
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:31,098
Never went fishing
or played catch

324
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:33,055
or even hugged each other.

325
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,185
We never danced
the hootchy-koo either.

326
00:13:34,271 --> 00:13:35,861
What's your point?

327
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:38,570
(voice breaking)
I just want you to know

328
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,241
that I love you, Dad.

329
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:42,069
-You do?
-(sniffles) Uh-huh.

330
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:45,204
Oh, son, I love you too.

331
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:46,782
Hey, how about a hug?

332
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,367
-Dad.
-Sonny-boy.

333
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:49,872
-Papa!
-Junior!

334
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,584
My old man.

335
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,584
Well, I got to go.

336
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:57,086
Oh, son, no. We got a lot
of catching up to do.

337
00:13:57,169 --> 00:13:59,259
Whaddaya say we go fishing?

338
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:01,668
Gee, Dad, if I wasn't on such
a tight schedule...

339
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:04,797
-(sniffles)
-Well, I--

340
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:07,295
Oh, let's get some worms.

341
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:10,808
Ooh! Oh!

342
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:11,811
Hey!

343
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:13,352
Well, no time for that.

344
00:14:13,435 --> 00:14:18,265
-(grunts)
-(chuckles)

345
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,647
Aw, I really wanted to
do that one.

346
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,783
-(grunting)
-I got you!

347
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:23,991
Aargh!

348
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:26,371
Gee, Dad, way to hog
my last moments.

349
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:28,328
Just a quick game
of hacky-sack.

350
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:33,905
I love you, son.

351
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:37,418
Yeah, yeah.
Gee, the old guy's a little love-starved.

352
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:41,131
Get moving, you hunk of junk.
I gotta make up for lost time.

353
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:42,343
-(siren wailing)
-D'oh!

354
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:46,549
(police radio chatter)

355
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:49,465
I'm sorry, officer.
I know I was going too fast.

356
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:51,305
-Just give me a ticket.
-I beg your pardon?

357
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,770
Just give me a ticket!

358
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:55,310
Whoa. That sounded
like an order.

359
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:57,904
I pay my taxes,
and they pay your salary.

360
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:01,860
So when I say give me a ticket,
just give me a ticket.

361
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:04,822
Uh-huh. Maybe we don't want
to give you a ticket.

362
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,364
Maybe we wanna haul
your butt in, wise guy.

363
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:09,408
(grunting)

364
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:12,331
OFFICER: Look what else your
tax dollars pay for, huh?

365
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:13,371
-(door slams)
-(officers laughing)

366
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:14,374
(whimpers)

367
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:21,344
♪♪ (harmonica)

368
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,801
That's sort of nice.
What are you in for?

369
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:28,894
Atmosphere.

370
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,809
Okay, flash,
you get one phone call.

371
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:35,519
Wait. I can't call Marge.

372
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,941
It's our last day on Earth
together.

373
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:38,349
I can't drag her into
this mess.

374
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:41,267
I know--
I'll call Barney.

375
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,437
(ringing)

376
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:46,605
<i>♪ Nobody's here, nobody's here,</i>
<i>nobody's here ♪</i>

377
00:15:46,695 --> 00:15:49,945
Damn those novelty telephone
answering machine tapes!

378
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,992
HOMER:
<i>Thanks a lot, Barney!</i>

379
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,576
<i>I just wasted my</i>
<i>one phone call on your--</i>

380
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:57,921
Wait! I'm home, I'm home.
Oh. Hi, Homer.

381
00:15:57,998 --> 00:15:59,578
You gotta help me Barney,
I'm in jail.

382
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:02,247
You are? Hey, Homer,
go to the window.

383
00:16:02,336 --> 00:16:03,586
Hi, neighbor.

384
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,261
I can see you!

385
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,720
{\an8}Aah! Just get over here
and bring 50 bucks for bail.

386
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:10,391
50 bucks?!

387
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,099
What did you do,
kill a judge?

388
00:16:12,179 --> 00:16:15,139
Where am I gonna get
50 bucks?

389
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:19,187
Hey. Pizza!

390
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:25,821
Why are we all
dressed up?

391
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:28,571
Because sometimes it's fun
to dress up for dinner.

392
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,324
Why are we using
the good china?

393
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:33,156
Because sometimes it's fun
to use the good china.

394
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,282
What's with
the candles?

395
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:36,328
Sometimes it's fun
to use candles.

396
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:37,752
Why are we waiting
for Dad?

397
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:41,380
Because we love your father
and enjoy his company.

398
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,338
Why are we really
waiting for Dad?

399
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:49,882
Ha! $48.70.

400
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:52,177
You know, we don't usually
take rusty money.

401
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:56,721
You're dying, and you weren't
even going to stop at Moe's

402
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:58,887
for a last beer
with your buddies?

403
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,226
(sobbing)

404
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:03,360
Hey Barney, look,
it was on my list

405
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:06,609
along with a lot of other things
I didn't get to do today.

406
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,192
Hey, my boss!

407
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:11,447
Smithers, check out the
luscious pair on that redhead.

408
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,280
That's it, baby.

409
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:14,485
Work those ankles.

410
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:15,825
Ring-a-ding-ding, sir.

411
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:18,829
{\an8}Hey, Burns!
Eat my shorts!

412
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:20,502
Who the Sam Hill
was that?

413
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:23,001
Why it's...
Homer Simpson, sir.

414
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,633
One of the schmoes
from Sector Seven-G.

415
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,050
Simpson, eh?

416
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:29,008
I want him in my office
at 9:00 Monday morning.

417
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:32,089
We'll see who eats
whose shorts.

418
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:34,086
HOMER:
Wow, of all the luck.

419
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:35,508
To think I almost died

420
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:38,016
without telling the boss
to eat my shorts.

421
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:40,428
Oh, Homer, come on.

422
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:42,727
You got time
for one last beer.

423
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:43,981
Please!

424
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,105
I got to call Marge.

425
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:48,731
Ha!
(makes whipping sound)

426
00:17:48,817 --> 00:17:51,067
-(ringing)
-Hello, Moe's Tavern.

427
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:52,863
Birthplace of the Rob Roy.

428
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:55,066
Is Seymour there?
Last name Butts.

429
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:56,577
Just a sec.

430
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:59,038
Hey, is there a Butts here?

431
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:01,579
Seymour Butts?

432
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:04,923
Hey, everybody,
I want a Seymour Butts!

433
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,420
(laughing)

434
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,632
Oh, wait a minute.

435
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:10,512
Listen, you little
scum-sucking, pus bucket.

436
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:12,379
When I get my hands on you

437
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:15,336
<i>I'm gonna pull out your eyeballs</i>
<i>with a corkscrew.</i>

438
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:19,221
Oh, it was busy.

439
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:22,846
Moe, another last beer,
please.

440
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:25,765
(sniffles)
Guys, keep it down.

441
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:27,864
I got some last words.

442
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:31,240
I never told you this before,
but sometimes when I'm at work

443
00:18:31,318 --> 00:18:33,648
I think of you and smile.

444
00:18:33,737 --> 00:18:35,277
So often I think that--

445
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:38,834
Oh, words won't do it.
I love you, Moe.

446
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:40,289
Please, not in public.

447
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:41,749
You better be dying.

448
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:42,869
I love you, Barney.

449
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:44,785
Whoa! How European.

450
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,503
-(belches)
-(screams)

451
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,713
C'mon, Barney.
I got to get home.

452
00:18:50,003 --> 00:18:51,843
Faster, Barney, faster.

453
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:54,012
I'm twirling
as fast as I can.

454
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,259
Oh, I can't wait any longer.

455
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:58,604
Hold on, Marge.

456
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:01,179
I'm coming home, baby!

457
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:03,345
(panting)

458
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:04,893
Come on, come on.

459
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:08,899
Oh, where can he be?

460
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:12,901
Marge! Marge!

461
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,565
Homer!

462
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:15,783
There's no time
to explain.

463
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:18,493
Love you, love you,
love you.

464
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:19,834
(gargling)

465
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,788
I wrote a poem for you
this afternoon, Homer.

466
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:23,749
It's called "To a Husband."

467
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:24,959
Okay, okay.

468
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:26,328
(clears throat)

469
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:28,325
"The blackened clouds
are forming..."

470
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:29,537
Oh, give me a break, Marge.

471
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:31,456
"Soon the rain
will fall.

472
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:33,205
"My dear one
is departing

473
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:37,627
"But first,
please heed this call

474
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:40,388
"That always
will I love you

475
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:42,930
My one, my love, my all."

476
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:44,925
That was beautiful.

477
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:48,152
(kissing)

478
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,777
(sighs)

479
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,952
Good-bye, Maggie.

480
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,084
Stay as sweet as you are.

481
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,996
Good-bye, Lisa.

482
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:10,791
I know you'll make me proud.

483
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:14,877
Good-bye, Bart.

484
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,013
I like your sheets.

485
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,684
The good book.

486
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:26,064
On tape?

487
00:20:26,141 --> 00:20:29,141
Ooh, it's read by Larry King.

488
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:34,187
<i>Hi, I'm Larry King.</i>

489
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:37,784
<i>In the beginning, God created</i>
<i>the Heaven and the Earth</i>

490
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:39,611
<i>and the Earth</i>
<i>was without form...</i>

491
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,986
<i>Alzeah begat Phineas,</i>
<i>Phineas begat Abushua, and...</i>

492
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:44,825
(tape fast-forwarding)

493
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,200
<i>...begat Ahamas,</i>
<i>Ahamas begat...</i>

494
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:47,866
(tape fast-forwarding)

